I seem to have an issue similar to http://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/12204

That is, I can start a new sandbox game, and try to launch the Kerbal X. Doing so gives me a very odd camera angle that I cannot change, and pressing Esc causes the vessel (which mods dont recognise at all) to rise out of the atmosphere. I have to Alt-F4 to get rid of this. The error has come up once in my career save also, but I dismissed it as I couldnt replicate it easily.

I see Kopernicus has updated, so Im going to update that and see if anything changes (EDIT: It didnt). Id appreciate any suggestions for troubleshooting. Thanks for taking the time to have a look.

Extra:

Going through the output_log.txt, I found a largely repeating section from ContractConfigurator complaining about a missing group, 'SpaceTuxGroup'. @linuxgurugamer is this expected? Im guessing its unrelated to the issue above, but there you have it.

6 hours ago, blu3wolf said:

Going through the output_log.txt, I found a largely repeating section from ContractConfigurator complaining about a missing group, 'SpaceTuxGroup'. @linuxgurugamer is this expected? Im guessing its unrelated to the issue above, but there you have it.

The three contract mods I have need some love, but, did you install them via CKAN or manually?

No, it is not expected behaviour, CKAN installs the SpaceTuxGroup automatically, so I would expect that you did this manually.

Here is a link to the missing group:  https://spacedock.info/mod/53/SpacetuxSA
